  "why": "The paper describes TESTRNN as a coverage-guided fuzzer that generates and evaluates fault‑inducing inputs against a given RNN under test, and all algorithms and experiments are framed as per‑model testing. The method and experiments do not include any explicit design to discover transferable failures (e.g., using surrogate models, ensembles, or cross‑model feedback) nor do they demonstrate reusing fault‑inducing inputs discovered on one model to test other, unseen target models. All generation and fitness computations are performed with respect to the RNN being tested, and comparisons across models are per‑model robustness measurements rather than transferability experiments.",
